import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    top_10_jobs = data.nlargest(10, 'count')
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='job', y='count', data=top_10_jobs)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What are the top 10 most common jobs in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    job_perc = data.groupby('job')['perc'].sum().reset_index()
    job_perc = job_perc.sort_values(by='perc', ascending=False)
    if len(job_perc) > 20:
        job_perc = job_perc.head(20)
    plt.pie(job_perc['perc'], labels=job_perc['job'], autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the percentage of people holding each job?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```
